reviews.review_text: Taping info The cassette master was originally transfered from a Kyocera D811 to a Sony PCM2600 in and around 1997. There was no Nakamichi 700ii and no generational loss due to a cassette/cassette dub. The master cassette is no longer available, as I can't find it. This is all that remains but still slightly betters the other 441 PCM version here on archive due to us being closer to the stage, which gives a slightly more upfront perspective.
